tive archives academic workshops stanford humanities research network the humanities research network provides workspaces for collaborative research teams working at a distance the workspaces include project calendars tools for co authoring documents a project journal and centrally archived email discussions go to stanford humanities research network spatial & gis special interest group stanford the spatial & gis special interest group stanford was formed around a common interest in working with spatial data and or gis particularly in the humanities and social sciences our mission is to facilitate multidisciplinary networking among faculty students and academic staff who apply gis spatial technologies and analytical approaches go to spatial & gis special interest group stanford tooling up for digital histories tooling up for digital histories is a collaboration between the spatial history project and the computer graphics lab at stanford university and many others to compile and create new tools for digital and spatial research in the humanities go to tooling up for digital histories stanford university all rights reserved stanford ca 94305 contact us school of humanities and sciences stanford humanities center
